lxtask
------------------------------------------
A lightweight and desktop-independent task manager derived from 
xfce4-taskmanager with all dependencies on xfce removed, new features, 
and some improvement of the user interface.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.1-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libglib2.0_0-2.22.4-2
  libgtk2.0_0-2.18.6-1
  libintl8-0.17-11

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.65-1
  automake1.11-1.11.1-1
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.80-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  gnome-common-2.28.0-1
  intltool-0.40.6-1
  libtool-2.2.7a-15
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://lxde.org/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/lxde/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack lxtask-0.1.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./lxtask-0.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/lxtask-0.1.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/lxtask-0.1.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

